{"id":"snap_468b6cd3c2f9955a","schemaVersion":"0.1.0","title":"Discover local Eve repositories","type":"feature","summary":"Eve now discovers sibling local repositories that already contain both .git and .eve, so a restarted web daemon can show existing Eve-enabled projects even if they were not previously written to the user-level registry. Registry writes now prune stale unusable entries, and tests isolate registry state away from the user config directory.","userVisibleChange":"The web UI can show another local Eve-enabled repo such as chaintalk after restart without requiring that repo to be re-recorded first.","relationships":{"corrects":[],"supersedes":[],"reverts":[],"dependsOn":[],"related":[]},"risks":[],"timeline":[],"decisions":[{"title":"Discover sibling Eve repositories by default","rationale":"Users expect existing local projects with .eve data to appear after restarting Eve, not only repositories touched by the newest binary."},{"title":"Keep discovery local and bounded","rationale":"Scanning the active repo parent with a shallow depth finds sibling projects without broad filesystem traversal."}],"validation":[{"command":"go test ./...","status":"passed"},{"command":"go test ./cmd/eve -run TestRuntimeDiscoversUnregisteredSiblingRepositories -v","status":"passed"},{"command":"printf list_repos request | go run ./cmd/eve mcp-stdio","status":"passed","output":"Returned eve and chaintalk, including chaintalk snapshot snap_080e0ffc02e9de0a."}],"artifacts":[],"implementation":{"branch":"main","gitState":"d611a01ca98b8a787cee0ad9e59bd9a547ec6fb7","commits":["d611a01ca98b8a787cee0ad9e59bd9a547ec6fb7","a70630dc38b54ae23be92a4ed7534dc0fbc15231","421a4b3fa6036fd4c80c79a8b7d8958bb4de0689","086d4b1a062217815329766876ef64eb68e1a516","0c67b4d5a92bc08418960b5fd97162e51d82cf28","33c758e074bc519e24b8dd68833f61c60592de37","cf72d7b4ce8a7af4c571b1a82e247552d8d452fb","57e13a38e8da0a7af68c9d234607b5a67dfb5263","59ac1cdd3eef684fb8bd1c05113dcb27903dd179","4652be12fd2a625b881f